@AkihiroSuda 

> Do you have benchmark data? (container->external via TAP, and external->container via the port forwarder)

Yes, [here](https://passt.top#perf_27). There are a few fundamental links in the [description](https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/16141#issue-1406598530).

@edsantiago
> Tests are very broken. This is an incomplete review, but am submitting because I can't spend any more time on this right now (it's been almost four hours)

I'm going over your comments soon, but can you please indicate in which way tests are _broken_? Indeed I ran them, and checked every single new helper I wrote in isolation, with bash 5.2.0 and bats 1.8.0. Note that they are also used by a number of tests in the CI. What did break exactly?

Oh! Forgot to mention: if you rebase on #16220 (which I expect will be merged), you will pick up the new `20221018` IMAGE, which includes `ip -j` and `socat`.  That image has already been built and pushed to quay. If you don't want to rebase, you can simply apply:
```diff
diff --git a/test/system/helpers.bash b/test/system/helpers.bash
index 4bc1ba78c..a1114494c 100644
--- a/test/system/helpers.bash
+++ b/test/system/helpers.bash
@@ -7,7 +7,7 @@ PODMAN=${PODMAN:-podman}
 PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_REGISTRY=${PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_REGISTRY:-"quay.io"}
 PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_USER=${PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_USER:-"libpod"}
 PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_NAME=${PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_NAME:-"testimage"}
-PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_TAG=${PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_TAG:-"20220615"}
+PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_TAG=${PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_TAG:-"20221018"}
 PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_FQN="$PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_REGISTRY/$PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_USER/$PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_NAME:$PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_TAG"
 PODMAN_TEST_IMAGE_ID=
 ```
